name: Project-order-manager-system-microservices
description: Order Manager System uses Spring Boot and Redis/MariaDB to manage orders, users, products, suppliers, and shipping on AWS EC2. CI/CD through GitLab/Jenkins, Resilience4j, Docker, and Postman support testing and deployment, along with Agile Scrum/Jira for project management.

name: Highway-Ticket-Management-System-Microservice
description: This is the Final Assessment of Microservices.

name: Employee-Management-System
description: This is a sample project made with microservices architecture for learning purposes

name: tickets-manager-with-microservices
description: A POC to explore how build complexy systems using microservices CQRS and queues

name: vts
description: Vehicle Tracking System as a set of REST APIs using Flask microservices.

name: irctc_backend_java
description: The IRCTC Backend Project is a Java based application designed to simulate a real-world train booking system. It supports user sign-up, login, fetching bookings, searching for trains, booking seats, and canceling bookings.

name: InfyRail
description: InfyRailMS is a microservices-based railway management system designed to streamline and automate various operations related to railway services. The system leverages Spring Boot and Spring Cloud technologies to provide a scalable and modular architecture.

name: End-to-End-Data-Pipeline-for-GitHub-Issue-Forecasting
description: Developed an end-to-end data pipeline using microservices (React, Flask, LSTM) for tracking, analyzing, and forecasting GitHub issue trends. The system processes real-time data, performs advanced trend forecasting with TensorFlow/Keras, and visualizes results using GCP.
